    "When a lepton radiates around the Z-mass, there is a significant effect, as the mass will be lower, leading to a migration from the Z peak to lower DY masses.",
    "At much lower (and higher) DY masses, QED radiation still occurs, but it arises from a continuous mass spectrum.",
    "The migration from higher to lower DY masses is negligible because of the falling DY invariant mass spectrum.",
    "The figure indicates that the radiating leptons contribute to pairs with larger transverse momentum.",
    "ConclusionThe study presented in this paper provides a detailed explanation of the influence of the Sudakov form factor on the determination of the parton intrinsic-k T distribution using the PB Method."
